A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing July 2025 as Muslim American Heritage Month; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia takes great pride in the varied religious and cultural
3 traditions of residents of this state and seeks to afford all people in Georgia the opportunity
4 to better understand, recognize, and appreciate the rich histories, cultures, significant
5 contributions, and shared principles of Muslim Americans; and
6 WHEREAS, Muslim Americans contribute greatly to charitable organizations that help
7 people from all faiths in the United States and around the world by feeding the hungry,
8 providing recuperation efforts following natural disasters, and providing medical assistance,
9 family services, scholastic supplies, and before- and after-school programs; and
10 WHEREAS, Muslim Americans have contributed to every part of the economy, culture,
11 education, and identity of Georgia and the United States in making advancements in
12 architecture, arts, business, culture, diplomacy, government, law, medicine, the military,
13 national security, religion, and sports; and
