14 WHEREAS, Muslim Americans from Georgia have made significant contributions in the
15 global fight against polio, malaria, influenza, hepatitis, and cancer and in the development
16 of vaccines; and
17 WHEREAS, there is a need for public education, awareness, discourse, and policies that are
18 culturally competent when describing, discussing, or addressing the impacts of being Muslim
19 American.
20 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
21 recognize the month of July 2025 as Muslim American Heritage Month at the state capitol
22 and encourage officials and departments of state, county, and municipal governments, boards
23 of education, elementary and secondary schools, colleges and universities, businesses, and
24 all citizens to participate in appropriate ceremonies, programs, and activities that
25 commemorate and honor the contributions of Muslim Americans throughout said month.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
27 to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to the public and the
28 press.
